		<h2 class='diff-currentversion-title'>Latest revision as of 15:06, 2 February 2015</h2>
<p><b>Counter-recruitment</b> is a strategy often taken up to oppose <a href="/wiki/War" title="War">war</a>. Counter-recruitment is an attempt to prevent <a href="/wiki/Military_recruiters" title="Military recruiters" class="mw-redirect">military recruiters</a> from enlisting civilians into the military. There are several methods commonly utilized in a counter-recruitment campaign, ranging from the <a href="/wiki/Politics" title="Politics">political speech</a> to direct action. Such a campaign can also target entities connected to the military, such as intelligence agencies, or private corporations, especially those with defense contracts.</p>
<p></p>
